<html><head><title>
PRESS RELEASE</title></head>
<body background="../Images/background.gif" bgcolor=#ffffff>
<p>
<font size=-1>
REI Providers Association<br>
1420 16th St., N.W., Washington, D.C.  20036<br>
Contact:	Randy Dyer, CAE<br>
Phone:		(202) 328-7460<br>
FAX:		(202) 332-2301<br>
e-mail:		<a href="mailto:reipa@aol.com">REIPA@AOL.COM</a><br>
Website:	<a href="http://www.reipa.com">WWW.REIPA.COM</a><br>
</font>
<p>
<b>
FOR IMMEDIATE RELEASE</b>
<p>
<font size=+1>
<b><i>MLS Roundtable merges with REI Providers Association</i></b>
</font>
<p>
Board Elects First Officers
<p><b><i>
Memphis, TN, June 17</i> </b>
-- The MLS Vendor Roundtable, an association of the
major multiple listing services, has voted to merge its operations with the
newly formed REI Providers Association (REIPA).

<p>
The MLS Vendor Roundtable is composed of more than two dozen providers of
residential multiple listing services across the country including industry
giants Interealty Corp., Moore Data Management Services, and Boris
Information Systems.  The Roundtable's members will now pursue their agenda
within the REI Providers Association.  "The decision to merge reflects a
belief on the part of the MLS industry that there should be an integrated
approach to real estate information," said Rick Roof, vice president of
Interealty Corp. and the Chairman of the MLS Roundtable.  "We can accomplish
a great deal more within the context of the larger industry Association."

<p>
At their meeting in Memphis, TN, on June 7, the REIPA Board of Directors
welcomed the members of the MLS Roundtable and agreed to form an MLS Task
Force which will be composed of mls vendors of all sizes  to begin to shape
the agenda for the future. 

<p>
The Board also appointed Tom Gay, Vista Information Solutions, San Diego,
CA, to head a second Task Force composed of Commercial Real Estate
Information Providers for the purpose of determining the ways in which the
Association can serve this segment of the industry.  It is expected that
both of these Task Forces will meet within the next 90 days to begin their work.

<p>
In other areas, the REIPA Board elected W.B. Freeman, Clareity Consulting,
LLC, Des Moines, IA, to serve as the Association's first President.  Rufus
Lusk III, TRW REDI Property Data, Washington, DC will serve as
President-Elect and will succeed to the Presidency of the Association
following Mr. Freeman's term on January 1, 1998.  Tony Stewart, Moore Data
Management Services, Minneapolis, MN, will serve as the Association's Vice
President for Membership.

<p>
The Board also confirmed the selection of two other officers.  Gilbert
Barnes, Data Track Systems, Carlsbad, CA will serve as the  REIPA Treasurer,
and Fred Baca, Baca Landata, Houston, TX, will  serve as Secretary. 

<p>
Finally, the Board announced a cooperative venture with GIS World,
publishers of Business Geographics, to offer a complimentary subscription to
the magazine to all members of the REI Providers Association.

<p>
The Real Estate Information Providers Association is a national Association
established to provide a forum for purveyors of information related to both
commercial and residential property as well as the application, support
services,  and other organizations associated with these efforts.

<p>
For further information regarding the REI Providers Association and its
activities, contact the National Office in Washington, DC at 202-328-7460 or
e-mail to <a href="mailto:reipa@aol.com">reipa@aol.com</a>.  The Association also welcomes your visit to its
internet website at <a href="http://www.reipa.com">http://www.reipa.com</a>.

</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO>WT05-B02-108</DOCNO>
<DOCOLDNO>IA081-000561-B021-456</DOCOLDNO>
<DOCHDR>
http://www.reipa.com:80/Industry/Press/pr033196.html 207.120.161.17 19970103125111 text/html 4521
HTTP/1.0 200 OK
Date: Fri, 03 Jan 1997 12:50:53 GMT
Server: Apache/1.0.5
