Last-modified: Tue, 25 Jun 1996 17:06:38 GMT
</DOCHDR>
<html><head><title>PRESS RELEASE</title></head>
<body background="../Images/background.gif" bgcolor=#ffffff>

<font size=-1>
<p>REI Providers Association<br>
1420 16th St., N.W., Washington, D.C. 20036<br>
Contact:	Randy Dyer, CAE<br> 
Phone:	(202) 328-7460<br>
FAX:		(202) 332-2301<br>
</font>
<p>
<b>FOR IMMEDIATE RELEASE</b>
<p><center>
<font size=+1><b><i>REAL ESTATE INFORMATION INDUSTRY FORMS TRADE ASSOCIATION
</font></i></b></center>
<p>
Charter Meeting to take place in Washington, D.C.
<p><b>
<i>Washington, D.C.,
March 31 </i></b>~ More than two hundred representatives of the real estate information industry will 
meet in Washington, D.C. on April 27, 1996, to charter a new trade association - the REI Providers Association.  
The meeting will take place at the Sheraton Washington Hotel.  The Morning Business Meeting will include 
ratification of the organizations bylaws, election of the Board of Directors, and the debut of the Associations 
dynamic now WebSite http://www.reipa.com.  Brad Inman -- a nationally recognized speaker -- will address the 
group at lunch.  The Afternoon Workshops will focus on issues of high priority to the industry at large, including 
government relations, data standards development, education and communication, and innovations in information 
technology.
<p>
The mission of the new organization will be to ensure that the public and business community will continue to have 
timely, accurate and reliable real estate information at their disposal.  To that end, the members of the REI Providers 
Association will work with legislators and regulators at the local, state, and national level to promote cooperation in 
the public interest.  By facilitating the free and efficient sourcing of public records data and by continually working to 
improve the quality of real estate information, the Association hopes to reduce costs incurred by consumers in the 
real estate transaction.
<p>
Membership in the REI Providers Association is open to professional organizations involved in the collection, 
maintenance, enhancement, and distribution of real estate related information, as well as those services which 
repackage this data or support any of these organizations operations.  Prospective members are grouped into four 
categories:
<p>
  Property Based Data Services, involved with information related to:  assessment, inventory, appraisal, 
property tax, flood zone, environmental hazard, sales and finance, listing, leasing, title and escrow, 
construction, building permit, and foreclosure.
<p>
<br>  People Related Data Services, involved with information reflecting:  census and household demographics, 
credit standing, crime statistics, bankruptcy, school data, telephone service, and business listings, etc.
<br>  Data Application Services, involved with the repackaging and resale of property and people related 
information include:  title insurance and mortgage lender market share analysts, GIS services, aerial and 
street mapping cartographers, mass appraisal services, property valuation systems, replacement cost 
services, property photo imaging vendors, etc.
<br>  Support Service Providers, providing professional services to the vendors and industry at large, include:  
geocoding and address hygiene services, data conversion services, software developers, consultants, etc.
<p>

The Chartering Committee, appointed at an industry meeting in Atlanta, Georgia in November 1995 includes W.B. 
Freeman, Envision Consulting Group, Des Moines, IA, serving as Chairman; Rufus Lusk III, TRW REDI, Silver 
Spring, MD, who serves as Vice Chairman; J. Fred Baca, Baca Landata, Houston TX; Gilbert Barnes, Data Track 
Systems, Carlsbad, CA; Jim Beczkiewicz, Interealty Corp., Oakbrook, IL; Garner Chandler, Chandler & Chandler, 
Memphis, TN; Tom Fore, Market Data Center, Norcross, GA; Tom Gay, Vista Information Solutions, San Diego, 
CA; and, Michael Hanrahan, Real Estate Software Advisors, Orange, CA.
<p>
Advising the Charter Committee on its work have been Mark Gidley of the Washington, DC law firm of White & 
Case and Randy Dyer with TASC, Inc., Association Management, also located Washington, DC.
<p>
If you need further clarification, please contact W.B. Freeman at (515) 255-2088 or e-mail the Association 
headquarters at <a href="reipa@aol.com">reipa@aol.com</a>.

</DOC>
