</DOCHDR>
<html><head><title>
PRESS RELEASE</title></head>
<body background="../Images/background.gif" bgcolor=#ffffff>
<font size=-1>
REI Providers Association<br>
1420 16th St., N.W., Washington, D.C. 20036<br>
Contact:	Randy Dyer, CAE<br>
Phone:	(202) 328-7460<br>
FAX:		(202) 332-2301<br>
E-mail:	<a href="reipa@aol.com">reipa@aol.com</a><br>
</font>
<p>
<b>FOR IMMEDIATE RELEASE</b> 
<p><center>
<font size=+1><b><i>REAL ESTATE INFORMATION INDUSTRY FORMS TRADE ASSOCIATION
</i></b></font></center>
<p>
Charter Meeting Takes Place in Washington, D.C.
<p>
<b><i>Washington, D.C., May 3 </i>
</b>More than 90 companies representing a broad spectrum of the real estate information 
industry met in Washington, DC on April 27, 1996 to form the REI Providers Association, creating a forum for 
developers and distributors of real estate information and the accompanying technology and support services.
<p>
In an all-day meeting, more than 140 representatives adopted bylaws for the new organization and elected the 
Associations first Board of Directors.  The program also included discussions of a number of important industry 
issues, from government relations and data standards to technology advancements.
<p>
It was agreed that the REI Providers Association will work to influence public policy at the state and federal level 
regarding privacy and access issues that affect the industry.  Moreover, it will monitor and educate the industry on 
implementation of data format and delivery standards to facilitate integration of all related data subsets and promote 
electronic collection and redistribution of data. It will also provide objective evaluation of advancements in 
technology relevant to those in the business.
<p>
The Association will also provide an electronic resource to the industry, with Internet access through the World 
Wide Web.  Through this site, participants will be able to access the Associations membership directory, hotlink to 
the websites of participating companies, and search the organizations files of industry information, and access an 
updated calendar of real estate industry conferences and conventions.  The Associations website will also serve as 
an industry yellow pages through which anyone interested in obtaining real estate information can access the 
membership product and service directory searchable by data type and jurisdiction.  The site, which is in the latter 
stages of development, can be accessible at http://www.reipa.com.  Prospective members can also use the sections 
within the website to request more information on the new Association  and to apply for membership.
<p>
The first Board of Directors elected to serve for the coming year includes:  Fred Baca, Baca Landata, Houston, TX; 
Gilbert Barnes, Data Track Systems, Carlsbad, CA; Jim Beczkiewicz, Interealty Corp., Oakbrook, IL; Garner 
Chandler, Chandler & Chandler, Memphis, TN; Tom Fore, Market Data Center, Inc., Norcross, GA; W.B. 
Freeman, Clareity Consulting, LLC, Des Moines, IA; Tom Gay, Vista Information Solutions, Inc., San Diego, CA; 
Rufus Lusk III, TRW REDI Property Data, Silver Spring, MD; Tony Stewart, Moore Data Management Services, 
Minneapolis, MN.  Mark Gidley, White & Case, Washington, DC, has been selected as general counsel.  Randy 
Dyer, CAE, TASC, Inc., Association Management will provide management services to the new Association.
<p>
For more information, please call 202-328-7460 or contact the Association via e-mail at <a href="mailto:reipa@aol.com">reipa@aol.com</a>.
<hr>


</body></html>
