<html>

<head>
<title>The Auburn Times</title>
<meta name="GENERATOR" content="Microsoft FrontPage 1.1">
</head>

<body bgcolor="#FFFFFF">
<p align=center><img src="/paper/images/timesttl.jpg" align=bottom width=397 height=67></p>
<p align=center><font color="#000000"><em>&quot;I am easily satisfied with the very best...&quot;</em></font></p>
<p align=center><font color="#000000"><font size=2><em>-Winston Churchill</em></font></font></p>
<p align=right><font size=2>Volume 1, Issue 4, January/1997</font></p>
<hr>
<p><font color="#00FF00"><font size=6>W</font></font><font color="#000000"><font size=5>elcome</font><font size=3> </font></font><font size=4>to the January edition of the Auburn Times! Thanks for dropping 
by, there's plenty to see, a good place to start is the</font><font color="#000000"><font size=4> </font></font><a href="../../editor.htm"><font color="#000000"><font size=4>Letter from the Editor</font></font></a><font color="#000000"><font size=4> but if 
you want to get right to the good stuff, then check out some wintery type 
articles worth plowing through like</font></font><font size=4> </font><a href="../../snowdays.htm"><font size=4>Snowdays, by Sara Guilcher</font></a><font size=4>, </font><a href="../../xmas.htm"><font size=4>Christmas 
Customs in other Countries</font></a><font size=4>, </font><a href="../../xmas2.htm"><font color="#000000"><font size=4>Christmas. . . it's not the great holiday for 
everyone</font></font></a><font color="#000000"><font size=4>, or </font></font><a href="../../xmas3.htm"><font color="#000000"><font size=4>Christmas Joy</font></font></a><font color="#000000"><font size=4>! See the latest duds in the </font></font><a href="../../fashion.htm"><font size=4>Fashion File</font></a><font size=4>, or get 
worked up over </font><a href="../../IBN.htm"><font size=4>International Buy Nothing Day</font></a><font size=4>. All you potential grads have a 
