<!DOCTYPE HTML PUBLIC "-//IETF//DTD HTML//EN">

<html>

<head>
<title>Auburn's Site Planning Strategy</title>
<meta name="GENERATOR" content="Microsoft FrontPage 1.1">
</head>

<body bgcolor="#FFFFFF">
<p align=left><font color="#408080"><font size=6><strong>Auburn's Site Planning Strategy</strong></font></font></p>
<hr>
<p><strong><u>Strategy Number One</u></strong>:</p>
<p><em>We will develop a financial plan that ensures the sustainability and improvement of 
programs and services.</em></p>
<p><u>Objectives:</u></p>
<ul>
<li>Identify Present funding for existing programs and services</li>
<li>Conduct a financial needs assessment for curricular and extra-curricular programs and 
services</li>
<li>Establish an annual budget process to allocate funds</li>
<li>Establish a process to ensure financial accountability</li>
</ul>
<p>&#160;</p>
<p><strong><u>Strategy Number Two:</u></strong></p>
<p><em>We will seek and develop partnerships with the total community to ensure the most efficient 
use of resources, facilities and opportunities for students.</em></p>
<p><u>Objectives:</u></p>
<ul>
<li>Cultivate a community resource data base</li>
<li>Expand business, community and educational partnerships</li>
<li>Establish effective communications within the community</li>
<li>Establish a orientation process for junior high students</li>
<li>Ensure and promote community access to the school</li>
<li>Establish a school council</li>
</ul>
<p>&#160;</p>
<p><strong><u>Strategy Number Three:</u></strong></p>
<p><em>We will develop and implement professional development programs for staff.</em></p>
<p><u>Objectives:</u></p>
<ul>
<li>Establish a professional development committee</li>
<li>Survey teaching and support staff to determine topics and priorities for ongoing 
professional development</li>
<li>Develop and implement a plan for professional development</li>
<li>Identify resources including personnel, materials, funding and time allotment</li>
<li>Inform school community of proposed topics and dates for professional development</li>
<li>Build morale and create a more comprehensive staff</li>
</ul>
<p>&#160;</p>
<p><strong><u>Strategy Number Four:</u></strong></p>
<p><em>We will develop procedures to ensure that technological advances and information 
retrieval and management are fundamental components of our programs and services.</em></p>
<p><u>Objectives:</u></p>
<ul>
<li>To provide professional development for all staff in the use and integration of information 
technology</li>
<li>To enhance communication and interaction within ADHS and our community through info. 
technology</li>
<li>To Efficiently coordinate information technology programs and services at ADHS</li>
<li>To identify and implement procedures which enable ADHS to effectively maintain its 
systems and standards in information technology</li>
<li>To acquire adequate funding to ensure the sustainablity and importance of technology and 
information retrieval at ADHS</li>
<li>To establish a committee to recommend school standards for the placement of new 
information and technology in ADHS</li>
<li>To establish a means of integrating information retrieval technology within all curriculum 
areas</li>
</ul>
<p>&#160;</p>
<p><strong><u>Strategy Number Five:</u></strong></p>
<p><em>We will develop and implement programs and services which will increase understanding 
and respect of diversities within the school and within the community</em></p>
<p><u>Objectives:</u></p>
<ul>
<li>To invite the school population, parents, and people from the community to become more 
involved with the school in promoting increased understanding and respect of diversities</li>
<li>To implement board and school policies on race relations, gender issues, and human rights 
so the it immediately becomes a permanent component in ADHS policy, programs and 
operations</li>
<li>To implement an anti-discrimination education program so that diversities are recognized, 
respected, and valued</li>
<li>To provide resources and materials to increase understanding and respect of diversities 
withing the school and community</li>
<li>To provide teaching strategies for staff and support services for the school population to 
increase understanding and respect of diversities within the school and community</li>
<li>To improve communication and interaction with the feeder schools</li>
</ul>
<p>&#160;</p>
<p><strong><u>Strategy Number Six</u></strong></p>
<p><em>We will improve services to students to meet changing social and educational needs.</em></p>
<p><u>Objectives:</u></p>
<ul>
<li>To improve awareness of existing services available to students</li>
<li>To ensure staff is given medical or family information that might have an impact on student 
behaviour</li>
<li>To provide info. to students, parents and staff on career options for non-university bound 
students</li>
<li>To develop and implement a student services program to meet the specific needs of 
students in each grade level</li>
<li>To establish a resource bank of staff and community members to provide a support group 
for student services</li>
<li>To make our student services to address the social and health needs of all our students</li>
<li>To improve availability and accessibility of information for university bound students</li>
</ul>
<p>&#160;</p>
<p><strong><u>Strategy Number Seven:</u></strong></p>
<p><em>We will pursue methods of improving academic performance.</em></p>
<p><u>Objectives:</u></p>
<ul>
<li>To develop a process for identifying the academic needs of incoming students</li>
<li>To implement a program for rewarding the achievement of academic and social goals by 
students</li>
<li>To establish self-esteem, peer helping programs that will help students take responsibility 
for their own success</li>
<li>To establish performance expectations in all courses</li>
<li>To develop and implement a home base/anchor program wherein each student has an 
advisor</li>
<li>To implement programs of academic and career counselling through enhanced student 
services</li>
<li>To enhance stay in school programs to support low achieving and at-risk students</li>
<li>To enhance anti-drug programs to at-risk students</li>
<li>To offer honours programs in core subject areas</li>
<li>To develop and implement a professional development program to support plans for 
improving academic performance</li>
</ul>
<hr>
<p align=right><a href="index.htm">Back To Main</a></p>
</body>

</html>
