<!DOCTYPE HTML PUBLIC "-//IETF//DTD HTML//EN">

<html>

<head>
<title>Hello , Welcome Back From Student Council</title>
<meta name="GENERATOR" content="Microsoft FrontPage 1.1">
</head>

<body bgcolor="#FFFFFF">
<p><b><i>Hello!</i></b></p>
<p><b>Welcome back to Auburn Drive for what is shaping up to be another great year for Eagle 
Spirit! </b></p>
<p>First of all, we would like to thank everyone who has taken the opportunity to get involved by 
coming out to spirit meetings, dances, participating in spirit days and helping us make warm 
fuzzies. Your support has helped make our first planed activities such a success.</p>
<p>If you're interested in increasing your school spirit here </p>
<p>is a list of upcoming activities that you can get involved in: </p>
<p>On Tuesday Oct.29 there will be <i>crazy </i>food tricks on the stage in the cafetorium. There will be 
chubby bunny contests, Jell-O eating races and pudding wars! If you are interested in participating 
in any of these messy games please sign up in the student council office later on in the week. </p>
<p>Halloween is a commin' and we have lots of crazy activities planned. Thursday of course is 
costume day. At lunch the costumes will be judged by the fine upstanding students of Auburn 
Drive in the gym. There will also be relay races, a candy toss and spook-O- grams will be sold 
for $.50. Sign up in the student council office if you are interested in helping out or participating in 
the relay races.</p>
<p>With November upon us we begin to look forward to some bigger events, starting with the year's 
first Unplugged on</p>
<p>Nov. 14. Make sure you come out and support the musical side of Auburn. This year's show 
promises to be a good one (as always) so come out and support our school's musical talent. </p>
<p>These are your up coming events here at Auburn. We are hard at work planning activities for the 
month of November. But don't forget we are always open to your bright new ideas. If there is a 
new committee that you would like to see formed or if you have a suggestion for a spirit day or 
school activity please feel free to come and tell one of us on the council. </p>
<p>We can't wait to hear your suggestions so please come in and talk to us any time of the day!</p>
<p>Yours in leadership,</p>
<p>Shelley Banks-President</p>
<p>Dave Pendlebury-Vice President</p>
<p>Doug Choo-Treasurer</p>
<p>Jesse MacLean-Secretary </p>
<p><a href="paprmain.htm">Back</a></p>
</body>

</html>
