<!DOCTYPE HTML PUBLIC "-//IETF//DTD HTML//EN">

<html>

<head>
<title>BISHOP'S UNIVERSITY David McCracken</title>
<meta name="GENERATOR" content="Microsoft FrontPage 1.1">
</head>

<body bgcolor="#FFFFFF">
<p align=center><b><u>BISHOP'S UNIVERSITY</u></b></p>
<p>Bishop's University is a place you go to have a good time and to get an education. Bishop's has a 
reputation as a party school. Yes, they provide adequate academics, but so do a lot of other 
schools. People come to Bishop's to get away from their parents, enjoy the football and to party.</p>
<p>One of the most liked things about Bishop's University is its small size. Total enrollment is only a 
meager 2500. This, combined with the small quiet town of Lennoxville, Quebec, provides a real 
sense of community. Class sizes are small with most first year classes not bigger than 35 students. 
Fourth year are generally under 20. With this small a University, the professors know your name, 
not your number. This small size does have its downfalls however, privacy is limited and the dating 
pool is small (very active however).</p>
<p>Academically, Bishop's will provide you with an education that you will need in the future. Bishops 
specialty is Business Administration, Psychology and Political Sciences. The school allows you to 
pick a wide variety of courses and you are not required to pick a major in your first year. 
Information on the courses available can be found on Bishop's homepage on the internet. The 
most popular bird courses are Canadian Economic development and Acting 101.</p>
<p>Back to the parties. There are two main places on campus to party and drink - The Pub (huge 
building, loud music, lots of people) and The Quiet Bar ( pool table, televisions, rock videos and 
regular party music). When there is a party, everyone knows about it. Residence parties are big 
events which usually have themes such as Octoberfest, or the famous naked parties and the 
belly-button shooter party. (the names tell all). The parties got so rowdy in the all male residences, 
they were made Co-Ed in an attempt to calm them down. The University has been working on 
ways of calming down the parties in order to lift its reputation. ( fight the power)</p>
<p>Sports are a big part of Bishop life. The Plex is the big athletics facility where everyone comes to 
workout and exercise. The football team &quot;Gaiters? is the pride and joy of the school and fans 
follow them where ever they play. For those not into sports and such, there are many extra 
curricular activities and clubs in the University.</p>
<p>To sum it up, Bishop's provides a good mix of education and fun to make a most memorable 
college experience.</p>
<p><b><u>Facts, Figs and other Stuff</u></b></p>
<p>Location: Lennoxville, Quebec</p>
<p>Total Enrollment: Approx. 2500</p>
<p>Male/Female ratio: 49:51</p>
<p>Percent of applications accepted: 68%</p>
<p>Percent of out of province students: 59%</p>
<p>Minimum admissions grade: 70% to 75%</p>
<p>Tuition: Approximately: $2000</p>
<p>Residence fee / 14 meals a week: $4126 to $4526 / year</p>
<p>Residence fee / 19 meals per week: $4224 to $4650 / year</p>
<p>Time limit for an undergraduate: basically there is none</p>
<p>Fashion: Casual and conservative. Women wear makeup, men clean shaved. Sweatpants, caps 
and sneakers are worn in the day, jeans at night. Wear stuff with Bishop's on it.</p>
<p>Best Parties: Rock for Recycling, Sigma Chi Disco Night, Frosh Week, Halloween Bash, Winter 
Carnival, Beach Party / Fashion show, Home Coming Football Game.</p>
<p>Drinking age: 18</p>
<p>Lennoxville is home to the Hell's Angels</p>
<p>David McCracken</p>
<p>Note: Information taken from The Real Guide to Canadian Universities - An Insider's Survey for 
Undergraduates. Edited by Sara Borins. 1994</p>
<p>&#160;</p>
<p><a href="paprmain.htm">Back</a></p>
</body>

