<html>

<head>
<title>Child Molestors - Sara Guilcher</title>
<meta name="GENERATOR" content="Microsoft FrontPage 1.1">
</head>

<body bgcolor="#FFFFFF">
<p align=center><font size=4><b>Child Molesters . . . why do we let them out of prison?</b></font></p>
<p align=center>by Sara Guilcher</p>
<p align=center>Recently in the media much attention has been given to child molesters. Richard MacFarlane has 
been in the public eye lately because he had breached the conditions of his release in that he 
moved near an elementary school in Rockingham. Hector Jesso, a violent sex offender, was just 
released from the Kingston Penitentiary in Ontario after serving 14 years. He was planning to live 
in Newfoundland so RCMP officials warned residents in the area. He could have as easily chosen 
Dartmouth, Nova Scotia. There has also been another admitted pedophile in the media lately, 
Ernest Warner. Ernest Warner was charged with 25 counts of stalking, sexual assault, attempted 
abduction, and the list goes on. He pleaded guilty to four stalking charges and served only two 
years in prison. After his release, Warner applied to become a foster parent and he was 
accepted! How can an admitted pedophile become a foster parent? </p>
<p>I am so grateful that I had a safe childhood and as I look at these incidents I am concerned for the 
children. Shouldn't someone be afraid? Why do we let these sick perverts dance along through life 
and get a second, and third, and fourth chance where they destroy the innocence of our youth? 
We let these monsters get away with so much it sickens me. We want to be known as a kind and 
forgiving society so we let them out of prison but yet we don't trust them. This is evident through 
the commotion that a pedophile generates when he or she moves into an area. Residents, 
especially parents, get upset and worried and don't want the pedophile living there. Why does the 
community worry and feel vulnerable, when after all, we forgave them as a society and we 
supposedly trust them enough to let them out of prison? We &quot; trust &quot; them but we don't want 
pedophiles living near schools, where children are easily accessible. It doesn't take a brain to 
figure out that children are everywhere, who's to say that these pedophiles won't go to another 
public place like the mall and find children? Why don't we trust these pedophiles? History has 
shown us not to... pedophiles often repeat their crimes over and over again until they build up their 
r&eacute;sum&eacute;s that we finally realize that yes these people are DANGEROUS. Despite our lenient 
justice system, none of us want to live with the consequences of our judicial system. </p>
<p>In California, Gov. Pete Wilson signed a law in September of 1996 that required repeat child 
molesters to be chemically castrated. California is the first state to make this bold and courageous 
move. Finally we are fighting back and actually punishing these offenders. This step taken applies 
to molesters who commit a second crime against a child under the age of 13. They must receive 
weekly injections of Depo-Provera, a drug that dampens sexual desire. European countries have 
used this method and the rate of repeat-offender has dropped from 100% to 2%.</p>
<p>We are wasting money and time by allowing sex offenders out of jail unimpeded. Castrate them all 
or throw away the key. Let them feel what it is like to feel helpless and have their freedom and 
innocence taken away. </p>
<p><a href="paprmain.htm">Back</a></p>
</body>

