<head>
<title>Coke or Pepsi? - Chrisitne Emberly </title>
<meta name="GENERATOR" content="Microsoft FrontPage 1.1">
</head>

<body bgcolor="#FFFFFF">
<p align=center>Coke&#153; or Pepsi&#153;?</p>
<p align=center>Christine Emberley	</p>
<p>It's an ongoing debate. Since there have been two different colas, there has been controversy over 
which is better. Coke&#153; is certainly more widespread. It has been around since the late 1800's 
and there probably isn't a continent on the planet that hasn't seen a can of it at one time or 
another. But in the past decade, Pepsi&#153; has been claiming that it's more popular. It's had its 
Pepsi Taste Test&#153;, which was a huge success. According to their statistics, more than 60% of 
participants chose Pepsi&#153; over Coke&#153;. But in Georgia (where Coke was &quot;invented&quot;, in 
Atlanta), you wouldn't find a can of Pepsi in a single store.</p>
<p>So, we here at Auburn Times want to know&#133; which do you prefer? Coke&#153; or Pepsi&#153;? This is 
an official A.T. poll, and your input would be greatly appreciated. E-mail us at 
941096@adhs.ednet.ns.ca with one of the following choices; Coke, Pepsi, Other (Please 
Specify), or Doesn't Matter.</p>
<p><a href="paprmain.htm">Back</a></p>
</body>

