<html>

<head>
<title>DENNIS' LIFE? DENNIS' STATE OF BEING - Dennis Mitchell</title>
<meta name="GENERATOR" content="Microsoft FrontPage 1.1">
</head>

<body bgcolor="#FFFFFF">
<p align=center><b>DENNIS' LIFE? DENNIS' STATE OF BEING</b></p>
<p>Hello again?... If there is anyone reading this? And if someone does read this please leave a 
comment because without your thoughts this writing may as well be on a piece of paper one 
million galaxies away, nowhere near intelligent life. (Not that you have to be intelligent to read 
anything I write.) So please if you do read it, I want feed back.</p>
<p>I was sitting in my friend's car, travelling without a cause or destination one night. The music was 
turned up, and my mind was tuned out. We drove up the crest of a large hill, and I could see a 
large part of the city. It was evening, and the lights made it seem alive. The feeling I felt was 
unexplainable. It was deeper than happy, not like when you're excited about something or when 
you meet someone new, or even when you accomplish something. I think, at that moment, if the 
universe were ripped in half, like looseleaf, I wouldn't care. I knew the city and those lights meant 
nothing, and the car I was in meaningless. Everything in my entire life that I ever thought of as 
important, or worried about, meant nothing at this moment. Everything concrete in my mind fell 
like broken glass. But, there was no feeling of being lost, or alone. I had this terrific force of 
motivation to do something great and express myself, and I knew deep down, that if I did this, my 
life would unfold. I also realized that I was the only one controlling my fate, except fate itself, and I 
decided to enjoy every moment I could because I was surrounded by all the uncertainties, and no 
matter what decision I made, it would be all right.</p>
<p>After writing this, and reading it over several times, I wondered if other people had a turning point 
in their life, and I decided that if there<i> was</i> a turning point<b> </b>in anyone's life, this was my turning 
point, and I had a direction. </p>
<p>I would tell you what my direction was, if I thought it would make a difference, but I want you to 
find your own path, because all decisions you make, if they are not for you, and don't come from 
your heart, you may die in some strangers bed, not knowing who you are. </p>
<p>You may wonder, what if I fail at what I love? Then I'll tell you: I would rather die an unsuccessful 
painter if that's what I like, than make one million dollars a day feeling meaningless, and wondering 
why I spend all those years of education to do something that has no meaning in someone else's 
life, <i>or mine</i>. I believe, that even if I knew now that I wouldn't make a cent doing what I like, I 
wouldn't stop for anything. And, I believe in myself, and know that I will die in my own bed, 
copious and complete by my own fate, fate itself. </p>
<p>Sign: <i>dennis mitchell</i></p>
<p><a href="paprmain.htm">Back</a></p>
</body>

</html>
