<head>
<title>Scholarships Made Easy - Rodney MacDonald</title>
<meta http-equiv="Bulletin-Text" content="">
<meta http-equiv="Bulletin-Date" content="">
<meta name="GENERATOR" content="Microsoft FrontPage 1.1">
</head>

<body bgcolor="#FFFFFF">
<p align=center><u>Scholarships made Easy</u></p>
<p align=center>By: Rodney MacDonald</p>
<p align=center>Well here it is, November already and everybody's talking about the future. Most people are 
finally realizing that this is their last year of high school and that they don't know where they will be 
one year from now. Everybody knows that to go anywhere nowadays you need to go to 
university, but have you thought about how you're going to pay for it? Sure, you could get a loan, 
and spend the next decade or so buried under debt. But there is a much easier way to go. Let the 
university pay! Scholarships are everywhere, and are just waiting to be claimed by ambitious 
students like you! What's that you say? Your marks are only so-so? You don't play sports? 
You're a social reject who doesn't participate in<i> anything</i>? No problem! Just print out the letter 
below, fill it out, and send it off to the school of your choice. Then just sit back and let the cash 
flow in. Easy as a cheezie! (WARNING!! Void where prohibited. May constitute fraud in some 
areas. Use of this letter relieves the author of any legal responsibility. Use at your own risk.)</p>
<p>Detach and $AVE $AVE $AVE!!!</p>
<p>------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------</p>
<p>Dear Sir or Madam,</p>
<p>I am writing in application for <u>(scholarship of choice)</u>. I possess many virtues which I believe 
would make me the ideal candidate for your award.</p>
<p>My name is <u>(your name).</u> I am a grade twelve student at Auburn Drive High School, where I have 
attained an average of 99.4%. I take only honors courses. If no honors course is offered, I 
provide my own extra credit work. I am heptalingual, speaking English, French, Swedish, Italian, 
Cantonese, Spanish and Japanese, all fluently. I am president of every club at my school, and I 
play the bassoon in my school band. Last year, I was invited to play with the Berlin Philharmonic 
Orchestra. Several times over the years, I have been urged to skip ahead a few grades. I, 
however have chosen to stay put, simply for the love of learning.</p>
<p>Outside of school, I work with many charitable organizations. I help the old, the poor (or &quot;the 
dirty people&quot;, as I like to call them), and homeless abused dolphins and koala bears. I always 
recycle and often pick through the garbage at the dump for objects that can be re-used or 
recycled. I hold down a part time job as a junior partner in a law firm. Last month, I prevented the 
deportation of thirty refugees.</p>
<p>I am an active participant in the arts community. Last year, I wrote a play and staged it on 
Broadway. It won seven Tony awards, including best actor (me, of course). I love sports. I am a 
ninth-degree black belt in four martial arts. Last summer, I swam across Lake Superior and 
climbed Mount Everest. Physically, my weight is in exact proportion to my height. My teeth are 
perfectly straight, and when seen from the proper angle, radiate light. My hair smells like apple 
pie.</p>
<p>I love Canada, rainbows, puppies and church. I love all people, except those who use the word 
&quot;can't&quot;.</p>
<p>So, please consider me for your scholarship. I would obviously be an asset to your university.</p>
<p><u>(sign here.)</u>	</p>
<p><a href="paprmain.htm">Back</a></p>
</body>

