<head>
<title>M&amp;M Question and Answer</title>
<meta name="GENERATOR" content="Microsoft FrontPage 1.1">
</head>

<body bgcolor="#FFFFFF">
<p>M&amp;M'S</p>
<p>QUESTION AND ANSWER	</p>
<p>QUESTION:	<i>A friend told me about a guy she thought would be perfect for me. </i></p>
<p><i>Should I call him for myself, or should I ask my friend to set up a blind date? </i></p>
<p><i>If I call him, what should I say?</i></p>
<p>ANSWER:	Ask your friend which procedure she thinks this &quot;perfect&quot; guy</p>
<p>prefers. Either way, your friend must talk to this guy, to make sure he wants to </p>
<p>meet you. If you do end up calling him, check to make sure your path is clear.</p>
<p>For starters say something like: &quot;Did Lisa say I'd be calling?&quot;, then say something</p>
<p>he wants to hear like: &quot;I hear you wanted to see this movie, I've been dying to see</p>
<p>it myself&quot;. If you are to shy to say something like that, say something like this:</p>
<p>&quot;It feels strange to be calling someone I've never met before, I hope you don't </p>
<p>mind&quot; . He will appreciate your honesty, and he will reassure you that he doesn't </p>
<p>mind you calling him (unless he does then he probably will tell you).</p>
<p>If the conversation goes well, casually mention that you would like to </p>
<p>get together (like if your going to a party, invite him to). Try not to take it </p>
<p>personally if your friend's idea of a &quot;dream guy&quot; turns out to be your worst nightmare, </p>
<p>she is trying to do you a favour and thank her for it.</p>
<p>IF YOU HAVE ANY QUESTIONS YOU WOULD LIKE US TO ANSWER:</p>
<p>WRITE TO 941119. ( or for outside people: 941119 @adhs.ednet.ns.ca) </p>
<p><a href="paprmain.htm">Back</a></p>
</body>

</html>
