<h1>About Timing Laboratory</h1>        
<IMG SRC="stripe.gif" ALT="----------------------------------"><p>

Timing Laboratory is a division of DollarLink Software.<p>

<A name="DlinkSoft"></a>

DollarLink Software is a ten-year old company primarily in the business of
developing technical analysis software for real-time traders.  <p>

Its main product is a popular technical analysis and charting software
package called <a href="dlink.htm">DollarLink</a>, which requires the use of a real-time datafeed
such as <a href="http://www.dbc.com">DBC-Signal</a>, Bonneville or 
<a href="http://www.pcquote.com">PC-Quote</a>.<p>

DollarLink Software also produces an electronic financial advisory newsletter
called <a href="dwin.htm">DollarWin</a> that specializes in mutual fund switching using a
called DollarWin that specializes in mutual fund switching using a
momentum-based technical analysis method. The model
portfolios recommended by DollarWin did very well in 1995; they were
up about 45% year-to-date on the average.<p>

DollarWin is broadcast daily by the <a href="http://www.dbc.com">DBC-Signal</a> datafeed as a
Signal Report and is available to Signal customers via the Signal
datafeed and on the Internet via <a href="dwin.htm">e-mail.</a><p>

Timing Laboratory produces the <a href="http://www.dollarlink.com">Select Timing Service (STS)</a>
mutual funds timing newsletter. STS is based on probabilistic
analysis of mutual fund price trends. It is available 
through the Internet.<p>

<IMG SRC="stripe.gif" ALT="----------------------------------"><p>
For more information, send us
<A HREF="mailto:timing-lab@dollarlink.com">an e-mail</A>.<P>

