<TITLE>Stop-loss Rule</TITLE>        

<!-- <BODY background="sandpapr.gif" color="#ffffff"> -->
<BODY color="#ffffff">

<A name="dettop"></a>
<h1>Stop-loss Rule</h1>        
<IMG SRC="stripe.gif" ALT="----------------------------------"><p>

As a safeguard, we use stop losses.  If our chosen fund starts dropping --
it can happen; after all, this is a game of probabilities -- we'll sell it
if it loses N percent or more from the purchase price, even if it means
getting hit with the 0.75% short-redemption penalty.  Thus, you may get a
new signal from us even if the month has not passed.  (We concluded from
our historical backtesting that N should be between 5% and 8%, but is
dependent on the fund's volatility.)<p>



