            ---------------------------------------------------
                      Commentary   (Friday 03/01/96)
            ---------------------------------------------------

Not a good week for the markets.  Talk of inflation and budget deficits
spooked traders and stocks lost about 2% for the week.  On Friday, the
markets recovered -- based in part on some economic reports -- and had a
strong positive finish.  Except for technology stocks which got killed
following Compaq's disappointing earnings report.  We are beginning to see
a divergence between the general market and technology, which is a pity
because technology fueled most of last year's rally and is capable of doing
it again this year.

We have changes this week in the 8-fund portfolio (replace Fidelity New
Market Income with Fidelity Select Chemical) and in the 4-Selects-only
portfolio (replace Energy with Defense/Aerospace).

