(*) The decision-making rules in DollarWin (technical analysis,
statistical, pattern recognition, etc.) are assigned a numerical value. 
Relative Strength Score (RSS) is a product of all these values.  The higher
the score, the better.  All the funds in the universe are ranked according
to this score.  "Risk" is a measure of recent (about 120 days) volatility
for each fund.  It usually varies between 1 and 30.  For mutual funds,
anything over 15 is considered very volatile.



