<TITLE>DollarLink News -- July 30, 1995</TITLE>

<!-- <BODY background="sandpapr.gif" color="#ffffff"> -->
<BODY color="#ffffff">

<A name="dlinktop"></a>

<center>
<IMG SRC="dlink.gif" ALT="[DollarLink Logo]"><p>
</center>

<h1>DollarLink News -- July 30, 1995</h1>

<IMG SRC="stripe.gif" ALT="----------------------------------"><p>


<h2>Enhancements Added</h2>

 
<h3>Symbols Dictionary</h3>

We've added the ability to create a symbols dictionary. Now you can 
call up the long company name associated with a symbol or comments 
about a particular symbol.  <p>

This feature allows you to easily enter detailed names of stocks, 
commodities, custom indices, etc. or to make notes to yourself.<p>

To access this feature, while in text mode, put the cursor over the 
target symbol and press the 9-key.  <p>

If the symbol is an option, DollarLink will just display its long 
name. Otherwise, DollarLink will search the dictionary file (called 
SYMBOLS.DCT ) for the symbol.<p>

If the symbol is not in the dictionary, DollarLink will ask you if 
you want to add a description sentence to the dictionary.  This is 
the way you would add entries to this dictionary.  (We do not supply 
symbol dictionaries with our software; the user creates his own customized 
dictionary.)<p>

If the symbol is in the dictionary, DollarLink will show its associated 
long name or whatever descriptive sentence you might have previously 
entered for this symbol.  It will also ask you if you want to modify 
the descriptive sentence.<p>

The file  SYMBOLS.DCT  is a straightforward ASCII file.  It can 
be modified (or created) with a word processor or text editor if you 
are outside of DollarLink.  The structure of each entry is simple: 
each line in the file consists of<p>

symbol name; description sentence.<p>

For example,<p>

<pre> 
IBM; International Business Machines 
AAPL; Apple Computers (makers of Macintosh) 
SP U5; S&P 500 Sept'95 futures contract 
$$SP;  Poor man's  S&P: futures from $SPX and $PREM 
INTC; bought Intel on 7/31/95 for 65 per share 
</pre>

<h3>More Checks on Options</h3>

For background equity options, during market hours, DollarLink can 
now ignore options that belong to stocks in your portfolios that have 
not traded today.  This helps eliminate  dead  options.<p>

To activate this feature, start DollarLink with the additional  DEADO  
word:<p>

$  DEADO  [enter]<p>

<h2>Updates Policy</h2>

Updates  with the above enhancements  will be available after 
the 15th of August.<p>

Updates are yours for the asking,  except  for those customers 
who bought DollarLink but have not paid the annual support & updates 
fee. The updates always have the latest updated manual included as 
a file on disk; new printed manuals are available for $20 to cover 
production and shipping costs.<p>

<IMG SRC="stripe.gif" ALT="----------------------------------"><p>

