<HEAD>
   <TITLE>Restoration Tips</TITLE>
   <META NAME="GENERATOR" CONTENT="Mozilla/3.0b5aGold (Win95; I) [Netscape]">
</HEAD>
<BODY TEXT="#000000" LINK="#0000FF" VLINK="#551A8B" ALINK="#FF0000">
<BODY BACKGROUND="pap42.jpg">
<P><BR wp="br1">
<BR wp="br2">
</P>

<CENTER><P><FONT SIZE=+2><B>Restoration Tips!</B> </FONT></P></CENTER>

<CENTER><P><BR wp="br1">
<B><FONT SIZE=+1>The Right thing to do!</FONT></B></P></CENTER>
<HR WIDTH="100%"></P>
<CENTER><P><BR wp="br2">
</P></CENTER>

<P><B>Restoration Tips</B>, a new and continuing feature of <B><FONT SIZE=+1>Pit-Stop's
&quot;Electronic Garage&quot;</FONT></B> is written by <B>John Paterek</B>,
a leading figure in the restoration of Porsche's for over 30 years. John
and his brother, Ray, have been involved in the preservation and/or restoration
of many of the world's finest cars, through their company, Paterek Brothers,
Inc., located in Chatham, NJ. His is a name well-know in serious collector
and Concours circles. <BR wp="br1">
<BR wp="br2">
</P>

<P>John has been on the Tech committee of the Porsche Club of America (PCA)
since 1985, and has been Head Judge for four National Porsche Parade, and
the Zone 1 PCA Concours for the past 16 years. He is a regular contributor
to the PCA's monthly magazine, Panorama, helping members with questions
about &quot;THE RIGHT THING TO DO&quot; to restore their Porsche to pristine
factory specifications. <BR wp="br1">
<BR wp="br2">
</P>

<P>John and his wife Donna are also very active in the <A HREF="http://www.pit-stop.com/nnjr">Northern
New Jersey Region (NNJR)</A> of PCA in concours events, swap meets, and
wherever auto enthusiasts need help in restoration projects. <BR wp="br1">
<BR wp="br2">
</P>

<P>We are very happy to have John's advice available to the wider audience
of <B>Pit-Stop, the Auto Enthusiasts' &quot;Electronic Garage&quot;! </B><BR wp="br1">
<BR wp="br2">
</P>

<P>In addition to his articles, John will publish here particularly interesting
questions, and his response, that he has received from enthusiasts. If
YOU have a question, email John! <BR wp="br1">
<BR wp="br2">
</P>

<P>John's initial material is presented below: <BR wp="br1">
<BR wp="br2">
<HR WIDTH="100%"></P>
</P>

<P>1. <A HREF="chiprepair.shtml">Paint Chip Repair</A> - And you thought
&quot;A little dab will do you&quot;!<BR wp="br1">
<BR wp="br2">
</P>

<P>2. <A HREF="paintmatch.shtml">Matching paint</A> - when it ISN'T NEW FACTORY
COLOR. <BR wp="br1">
<BR wp="br2">
</P>

<P>3. <A HREF="mirrors.shtml">Porsche 911 C2 Mirrors</A> - How hard are they to replace?
<BR wp="br1">
<BR wp="br2">
</P>

<P>4. <A HREF="guages.shtml">Instrument Guages</a> - Do yours need cleaning or &quot;prettying up&quot;?
<BR wp="br1">
<BR wp="br2">
</P>

<P>5. <A HREF="trim.shtml">Outside metal trim? </A>&nbsp;- How to restore it on the Targa.
<BR wp="br2">
<BR wp="br1">
</p>

<p>6. <A HREF="boschlights.shtml">Original Bosch Headlights</A> - How to clean
them up?</P>

<P>7. <a HREF="deposits.shtml">Water Spots or Acid Rain?</A> - Does it really matter?  I want them gone!</P>

<P>8. <A HREF="muffler.shtml">Mufflers</A>&nbsp;- How do you clean up these filthy things to repaint?</P>
<p>&nbsp;</P>

<p><center><font size=+1>Your question not here?&nbsp;&nbsp;<a href="mailto:donnap@mail.idt.net">E-mail John!</a></font></center></p>
<BR wp="br2">
<HR WIDTH="100%"></P>
</P>

