<DOCHDR>
http://stover.web.galaxy.net:80/restore/mirrors.shtml 207.111.84.73 19970208020806 text/html 3141
HTTP/1.0 200 OK
Date: Sat, 08 Feb 1997 02:08:14 GMT
Server: Apache/1.1.1
Content-type: text/html
</DOCHDR>
<!DOCTYPE HTML PUBLIC "-//IETF//DTD HTML 3.2//EN">
<HTML>
<HEAD>
   <TITLE>Non-Factory Tinted Paint</TITLE>
   <META NAME="GENERATOR" CONTENT="Mozilla/3.0b5aGold (Win95; I) [Netscape]">
</HEAD>
<BODY BACKGROUND="pap42.jpg">

<H1 ALIGN=CENTER>Restoration Tips! </H1>

<CENTER><P><B><FONT SIZE=+1>By John Paterek</FONT></B> </P></CENTER>

<CENTER><P>
<HR WIDTH="100%"></P></CENTER>

<CENTER><P><B><FONT SIZE=+2>Question</FONT></B> </P></CENTER>

<P>&quot;I own a '90 <B><FONT COLOR="#008000">911 C2</FONT><FONT COLOR="#E50000">
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#FFFF00"><FONT SIZE=+1>with early style mirrors</FONT></FONT></B>.
I recently purchased a pair of Aero Style mirrors in a kit from <B><FONT COLOR="#FF0000">AJ
U. S.A</FONT><FONT COLOR="#408000">.</FONT></B> Can I install them by myself?&quot;
</P>

<P>
<HR WIDTH="100%"></P>

<CENTER><P><B><FONT SIZE=+2>Response</FONT></B> </P></CENTER>

<P>The new style mirrors will <B>fit </B>door frames from 1978<B><FONT COLOR="#008000">SC</FONT></B>
on. The wiring will work from '87 <B><FONT COLOR="#008000">Carrera</FONT></B>
to the <B><FONT COLOR="#008000">C2</FONT></B>. For earlier cars the power
leads must be modified or purchase Manual (lighter) mirror kit 964 731
901 0 1. It is about $120.00 less and available from <B><FONT COLOR="#FF0000">AJ
U. S.A</FONT></B>. The assembly of the mirror base and headpiece is difficult
sometimes requiring 2 people to compress a rather large tension spring
and lock bolt. Be certain your new paint is dry or you will mar the surface
when assembly is attempted. The mirrors can be painted prior to assembly
of components. Before the mirrors are ordered it would be wise to unbolt
the mirror from your <B><FONT COLOR="#FF0000">Porsche</FONT></B>. Check
to see if the doors were repainted, any paint other than the factory baked
enamel will show a sink line under the gasket. It can be sanded with 1200
&amp; 2000 grit and buffed with <B><FONT COLOR="#408000">Blue Magic</FONT></B>
and <B><FONT COLOR="#FF0000">3M</FONT><FONT COLOR="#408000"> Imperial Hand
Glaze</FONT></B>. If the repair shop failed to remove the mirror when painted,
you will have a dead edge tape mark. The new mirror base is oval in shape
to the square style prior to '91. If not covered, a flaw will be quite
evident. The new mirrors make a great presentation, now all you need are
<B><FONT COLOR="#408000">RS America</FONT></B> 17&quot; wheels! <BR wp="br1">
<BR wp="br2">
</P>

<P>
<HR WIDTH="100%"></P>

<P><BR wp="br1">
<BR wp="br2">
</P>

