<TITLE>Searching the UC SAREP Cover Crop Database</TITLE>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#ffffff">
<IMG ALIGN=left SRC="/Images/cc_headr.gif" ALT="Working Icon">
<IMG SRC="/images/working.gif" ALT="Cover Crop Icon  " ALIGN="right">
<BR CLEAR=all><HR>

<A NAME="crops"></A><H2><CENTER>Searching the UC SAREP Cover Crop Database </CENTER></H2>

<FONT SIZE="+2">T</FONT>he cover crop database contains over 40 crop species that can be used as cover crops.  
Each crop description consists of up to 50 different subject categories.  When you query 
the database every subject category in the database is searched.  If a match is found a link 
will be returned to the specific crop subject category that was matched, as well as 
link to the full description of the crop (which contains the entire listing of information about the crop).<P>

The cover crop database now accepts queries seperated by AND, OR, and NOT. <img src="/images/new.gif"><P>

<form method=GET action="/cgi-win/ccrop.exe/search_ccrop">
<B>Search the cover crop database for a specific keyword:</B><BR>
<input name="searchstr" size=20> <input type=submit value="Search">
</form>
<PRE>

</PRE>

<A NAME="ref"></A><FONT SIZE="+2">W</FONT>ithin the subject fields of the cover crop database great pains 
have been taken to properly reference the information where needed.  If you would like to view 
a bibliographic references found within the cover crop database you can search here for the reference.<P>

Again, this utility only accepts a single word or a string of characters.  It is best searched by writing the first few characters of an authors last name.  For example 'Smith".<P>

<form method=GET action="/cgi-win/ccrop.exe/search_author">
<B>Search for an author or reference found in the cover crop database:</B><BR>
<input name="searchstr" size=20> <input type=submit value="Search">
</form>
</UL>

