<I>February 4
-5, 1997</I><BR>
<B>Nevada Regional Alfalfa Symposium</B><BR>
The Nevada Regional Alfalfa Symposium "Quality Alfalfa for All Markets" will be held on February 4th and 5th in Fallon, Nevada.  The syposium is geared to alfalfa producers and users.  Some of the topics include: Preservatives, Nutrition, Web Marketing, Russian Wheat Aphid, Subsurface Drip Irrigation, and Precision Farming.  There will be a post-conference tour of the new Top Gun training facility.  For registration and conference information contact Tim Stevenson, Pershing County Cooperative Extension, 702-273-2923 or tstevens@fs.scs.unr.edu.<BR>
<I>From: University of Nevada Cooperative Extension</I>
