<B>California Soil Quality:  From Critical Research to Sustainable Management</B><BR>
The M. Theo Kearney Foundation of Soil Science, an endowment-supported program in the Division of Agriculture and Natural Resources of the University of California, will sponsor a one-day symposium to bring Cooperative Extension personnel together with the Principal Investigators of the research projects currently supported by the Foundation.  The purpose of the symposium is to stimulate a dialog concerning the goals and methodologies of Kearney-supported 
research in respect to soil quality issues in California.
Attendance is by invitation.  Full information can be found
at the Kearney Foundation web site:<br>
