<I>April 25
-27, 1997</I><BR>
<B>California Grazing Academy</B><BR>
This unique and exciting three-day program emphasizes the
practical application of controlled grazing principles to improve the environment and increase ranch profit. This challenging course consists of a minimum of lecture and a maximum of hand-on experience and learning. Participants work in teams and get their own herd of cattle and ranch to manage during the Academy.  In addition, innovative hardware ideas are demonstrated and applied including: livestock watering systems, fencing, and many other ideas.

The Grazing Academy is taught by University of California Cooperative Extension Advisors Dave Pratt and Roger Ingram. The cost is $145 and includes course materials, meals, and lodging.

For more information, contact Roger Ingram, 11477 E Avenue, 
Auburn, CA  95603. Telephone 916-889-7385, Fax 916-889-7397.<BR>
