<HTML><HEAD>
<TITLE>People: Dave Campbell</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR = #ffffff><IMG ALIGN=left SRC="/Images/sarephdr.gif" ALT="Header Icon"><BR CLEAR=all><HR>
<font size="+3"><center>Dave Campbell</font><br>
<font size="+2">Community Development & Public Policy Analyst<p>
Sustainable Agriculture Research and Education Program<br>
(916) 752-7541<br>
FAX: (916) 754-8550<br>
<A HREF="mailto:dave.c.campbell@ucdavis.edu">dave.c.campbell@ucdavis.edu</A><br>
</font></center>
<p><hr><p><blockquote>
Dave Campbell is the Community Development and Public Policy Analyst for the University of California Research and Education Program (SAREP), where he works with Gail Feenstra to develop SAREPs program linking sustainable agriculture to community development and public issues. His other half-time position is as Director of the California Communities Program, an applied research and outreach unit of the UC Division of Agriculture and Natural Resources housed in the Human and Community Development Department at UC Davis. From 1990-95 he taught local government and public policy in the UC Davis Department of Political Science. For the past three years he has been a member of the steering committee of the California Alliance for Sustainable Agriculture (CASA), a coalition of non-profit groups and university programs funded by the W.K. Kellogg Foundation. He considers all this work appropriate penance for having grown up laughing at his quirky gardener Grandmother and her compost pile next to the outhouse. He now has his own compost pile, and a slug-infested garden, but not, alas, an outhouse. When hes not trying to save the world he enjoys writing and reading poetry.<BR>
  <BR>
   <P>
<P>
<P>
<BR>
</blockquote>
<B>Current/Past Projects:</b><blockquote>Sustainable Agriculture and Community Development Project (funded by W.K. Kellogg as part of the California Alliance for Sustainable Agriculture);<BR>
Steering Committee, California Alliance for Sustainable Agriculture<BR>
Community Development and Public Issues Workgroup<P>
<P>
<P>
</blockquote>
