<html>

<head>
<title>Elegant Brochure</title>
<meta name="GENERATOR" content="Microsoft FrontPage 1.1">
</head>

<body bgcolor="#FFFFFF">
<IMG SRC="/Images/sarephdr.gif" ALT="SAREP Header Icon"  ALIGN=LEFT><BR CLEAR=all>
<HR>
<img src="SustAgWorkGroup.gif" vspace=20 align=right width=200 height=134>
<center>
<h2>SUSTAINABLE AGRICULTURE EDUCATION WORKSHOP AND INFORMATION FAIR</h2>


<h3><i>November 22, 1996</i> <br>
<i>Buehler Alumni Center</i> <br>
<i>University of California, Davis</i> 
</h3>

<br clear=all>
<p align=center><b><i>Sponsors:</i></b> <br>

<i>UC Sustainable Agriculture Research &amp; Education Program</i> <br>
<i>UC Vegetable Research &amp; Information Center</i> <br>
<i>UC Fruit / Nut Research &amp; Information Center</i> <br>
<i>UC Davis Student Experimental Farm</i> <br>
<i>CDFA Fertilizer Research &amp; Education Program</i> <br>
<i>Community Alliance with Family Farmers Foundation</i> <br>
<i>California Association of Resource Conservation Districts</i> <br>
<i>USDA&#151;Sustainable Agriculture Research and Education Program</i> </p>
</center>

<p><b>WHO SHOULD ATTEND</b> </p>
<p>This workshop is designed for sustainable agriculture educators including teachers, extension advisors, consultants, non-profit organizations, private 
companies, government agencies or other groups. Participants will: </p>
<ul>
<li>hear about the variety of educational efforts and approaches currently underway in California </li>
<li>share educational materials related to sustainable agriculture </li>
<li>discuss where better coordination of activities and programs is needed </li>
<li>identify appropriate and useful communication links for organizations and groups involved in sustainable agriculture education </li>
<li>learn how to improve the quality and effectiveness of their educational efforts </li>
</ul>
<p><b>WORKSHOP OBJECTIVES</b> </p>
<ul>
<li>Increase the <b>communication </b>and <b>cooperation</b> among the many organizations and groups involved in sustainable agriculture education in California. </li>
<li>Look for ways to enhance the <b>educational process</b> through innovative curriculum and teaching methods </li>
</ul>
<p><b>AGENDA</b> </p>
<blockquote>
<p>8:00 <b>Registration and Information Fair Set-up</b> </p>
<p>8:45 <b>Welcome and Introduction</b> </p>
<p>9:00 <b>Concurrent Sessions</b> </p>
<ol>
<li><i>Weaving Sustainable Agriculture into Traditional / Mainstream Curricula and Programs.</i> </li>
<li><i>Sustainable Agriculture Education for Non-English Speakers.</i> </li>
<li><i>Biologically Integrated Orchard and Farming Systems (BIOS/BIFS) as a Model for Extension Education.</i> </li>
<li><i>Decision Cases: A Method for Teaching Critical Thinking and Systems Perspective in Agriculture </i></li>
</ol>
<p>10:15 <b>Break</b> </p>
<p>10:30<b> Concurrent Sessions Above Repeated</b> </p>
<p>11:45 <b>Lunch (seasonal buffet of salads and sandwiches)</b> </p>
<p><b>Information Fair</b> </p>
<p>Time for participants to interact with each other and to showcase educational materials, curricula, and programs. </p>
<p>1:30 <b>Communication Needs: Enhancing Interaction and Collaboration</b> </p>
<p>2:00 <b>Facilitated Workgroup/Action Sessions</b> </p>
<p>Share program ideas and address needs and opportunities for particular audiences. Participants select their workgroup based on their primary audience. 
We'll be addressing educational needs and opportunities for: </p>
<ol>
<li><i>Farmers and ranchers</i> </li>
<li><i>University, college, community college students</i> </li>
<li><i>Ag professionals</i> </li>
<li><i>Homeowners and gardeners</i> </li>
<li><i>K-12 students</i> </li>
</ol>
<p>4:30 <b>Workshop ends</b> </p>
</blockquote>
<p><b>HOW TO GET THERE</b> <br>
<blockquote>
The Buehler Alumni Center is located at the Southeast corner of Old Davis Rd. and Mrak Hall Drive on the UC Davis Campus. From I-80, take the UC 
Davis exit. Turn North on Old Davis Rd. and follow it as it turns East along Putah Creek. Parking permits are required; may be purchased at the entrance 
to the lot. </p>
</blockquote>
<b>REGISTRATION AND FEES</b> <br>
<blockquote>
