<h3 align=center>1995<br>
<font size=5>UNIVERSITY OF CALIFORNIA COOPERATIVE EXTENSION </font></h3>
<h3 align=center>PRODUCTION PRACTICES AND SAMPLE COSTS<br>
FOR ORGANIC COTTON </h2>
<h3 align=center>NORTHERN SAN JOAQUIN VALLEY<br>
</h3>
<p><a href="#OVERVIEW"><b>1995- U.C. Cooperative Extension Overview of Organic Cotton Production in the Northern San Joaquin Valley</b></a><b><br>
</b><a href="#COST"><b>1995 - U.C. Cooperative Extension Organic Cotton Cost and Return Study in the Nothern San Joaquin Valley</b></a><b><br>
</b><a href="#ASSUMPTIONS"><b>Cost of Production Assumptions for Organic Cotton in the Northern San Joaquin Valley</b></a><b><br>
</b><a href="#Ordering"><b>Ordering Information </b></a></p>
<p><b>Prepared by:<br>
</b>Karen Klonsky Extension Economist, Department of Agricultural Economics, U.C. Davis<br>
Laura Tourte Postgraduate Researcher, Department of Agricultural Economics, U.C. Davis<br>
Sean Swezey Entomologist, Farm Extension, Center for Agroecology and Sustainable Food Systems, U.C. Santa Cruz<br>
<A HREF="/sarep/staff/staff6.html">David Chaney</A> Information Analyst, Sustainable Agriculture Research and Education Program, U.C. Davis</p>
<p><b>Contributing Authors:<br>
</b>Pete Livingston Staff Research Associate, Department of Agricultural Economics, U.C. Davis<br>
Ron Vargas Farm Advisor/Interim Cotton Specialist, Madera County <br>
Bill Weir Farm Advisor, Merced County</p>
<p><b>Cooperating Growers:<br>
</b>Claude &amp; Linda Sheppard Sheppard Farms, Chowchilla, California </p>
